# Kubernetes Rules for ML

## Critical Invariants
- NEVER `uvicorn --workers N` in any Deployment — always `--workers 1`, HPA provides horizontal scale (D-01)
- HPA uses CPU only — NEVER `memory` as a metric for ML pods (fixed RAM footprint prevents scale-down) (D-02)
- NEVER bake model artifacts into Docker images — use Init Container + `emptyDir` volume (D-11)
- ALWAYS use Workload Identity (GCP) / IRSA (AWS) — no hardcoded credentials in pods
- ALWAYS verify `kubectl config current-context` before applying manifests
- NEVER overwrite existing container image tags — tags are immutable; use `sha`-pinned digests

## HPA Pattern (correct)
```yaml
metrics:
  - type: Resource
    resource:
      name: cpu          # CPU only — never memory
      target:
        type: Utilization
        averageUtilization: 70
```

## Init Container Pattern (correct)
```yaml
initContainers:
  - name: model-downloader
    image: google/cloud-sdk:slim
    command: ["gsutil", "cp", "gs://$(MODEL_BUCKET)/$(MODEL_PATH)", "/models/model.joblib"]
    volumeMounts:
      - name: model-storage
        mountPath: /models
volumes:
  - name: model-storage
    emptyDir: {}
```

